# Nested project repos — each has its own git repo (AGENTS.md: internal projects use
# their own repos). They must NOT be embedded as gitlinks in the workspace: a fresh
# clone can't fetch them, and every internal commit flags a spurious "M". Git can't
# track individual files (e.g. CONTEXT.md) inside a nested repo anyway — routing reads
# them off-disk. So ignore each repo dir wholesale. Enforced by .hooks/nested-gitlink-gate.sh.
academy/papers/2027-CHI-cria
academy/papers/ai4good
academy/papers/mechanism-search
academy/papers/mutual-credit-ai
academy/papers/pls-pix
branches/casinhas
branches/instituto
code/cria
code/gira
code/laplata
